{
  "stem": "2581.7",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But for a long time, my father was laying on his back-- on his stomach, couldn't lay on the back.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And a lot of people felt hurt because my father was respected in town.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And that's what they did.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They picked on individuals where it affected, psychologically, everyone in town.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They took the most respected citizen-- citizens in town and they humiliated them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "That was gradually, gradually too, you know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And it worked.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It worked to try to-- to keep up to this [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "First, they took the synagogue and they made it into a stable.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They they took the beth midrash.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You asked me about synagogues.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I forgot, but it was a beth midrash where people were sitting and learning day and night, day and night.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Synagogue, you know, was a more-- wouldn't use the word elegant, but it wasn't used for those purposes.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In a beth midrash, people would sit-- it was a forum-- and argue and learn.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "From this they made-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] what is it called?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "A milk-- a dairy farm, you know, where you put cows in and they milked.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they produced the milk for-- everything for the German population.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the fact is that they didn't realize that there were so many [NON-ENGLISH] in our town.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A lady that lived next door where we had our shop, every morning when she would see me when I was a child, she would pat me on the head, [NON-ENGLISH], you know, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My Polish nickname was [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She would give me a candy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I would say thank you.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, in Polish language, Miss-- you don't say Miss, but at the end of the name is-- like her name was Green, it was Greenovna.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Greenovna is a Polish name.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
